   THE&TABS$COMMAND PUTS EDIT INTO TABS MODE. WHEN EDIT IS IN TABS MODE
   WILL AUTOMATICALLY GENERATE 3270 HARDWARE TAB CHARACTERS FOR EACH COL
   POSITION ON THE SCREEN THAT CORRESPONDS TO A &*$ CHARACTER IN THE TAB
   PROVIDED THAT THE CORRESPONDING SCREEN POSITION IS BLANK.

        &SELECT OPTION ===> TABS          $ PUTS EDIT INTO TABS MODE.

   HARDWARE TAB CHARACTERS CAN BE FORCED TO OVERLAY NON-BLANK CHARACTERS
   SCREEN BY USING A PARAMETER WITH THE TABS COMMAND.

        &SELECT OPTION ===> TABS ANY      $ PUTS EDIT INTO TABS MODE, OV
                                              NON-BLANKS ON THE DISPLAY

   WHEN "TABS ANY" IS USED, OVERLAYED CHARACTERS WILL NOT APPEAR ON THE
   BUT THEY STILL EXIST IN THE DATA, AND WILL REAPPEAR ON THE SCREEN WHE
  &NOTABS$COMMAND, OR A SIMPLE&TABS$COMMAND IS ISSUED.

   THE&NOTABS$COMMAND CAN BE USED TO TAKE EDIT OUT OF TABS MODE.
